Class TemporalObject<T>

java.lang.Object
  xxl.core.pipes.elements.TemporalObject<T>
Type Parameters:
T -
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, TimeStampedObject<T>
public class TemporalObject<T>
extends Object
implements Serializable, TimeStampedObject<T>

A TemporalObject is a tuple consisting of an Object and a TimeInterval.

Since:
1.1

assignRandomTimeInterval

public static final <T> Function<T,TemporalObject<T>> assignRandomTimeInterval(long seed,
                                                                               int startInc,
                                                                               int maxDuration)
                                                                    throws IllegalArgumentException
Assigns a random time interval to a given value. The resulting sequence of time intervals is increasing with start = start+random.nextInt(startInc).

Type Parameters:
T -
Parameters:
seed - seed of the PRNG
startInc - the increment is equally distributed in [0, startInc-1]
maxDuration - the length of the timeinterval is equally distributed in [1, maxDuration]
Returns:
new instance for the given value with a random time interval
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException
